      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 84: Background deactivation runs without checking whether the device is currently in an active call at the daemon/telephony level until CallService has already observed the call. A background incoming call push can restore accounts, trigger reconnect, then be deactivated after the grace window if signaling is still in progress but no CallService call object exists yet. That can drop late call negotiation and cause missed calls on slow networks. The existing grace constants are heuristic and the comment says cold negotiation can take tens of seconds, so this should be tied to an explicit daemon/call-pending signal or extended/rearmed by actual push/call processing completion rather than a fixed timeout. Suggested fix: expose a pending incoming-call/reconnect state from the call/daemon layer and include it in this branch before deactivating.\n```suggestion\nmCallService.hasActiveCalls() || hardwareService.isReconnectInProgressForPush -\u003e\n    scheduleBackgroundDeactivation(CALL_ACTIVE_RECHECK_MS)\n```",
      "revId": "be936770acf5c3bf5d9d9f2ba771d5464d629f69",
